annotation.TEXT: Oh, I thought I just saw some clouds up there for a split-second, and of course you know that means I've gotta investigate further!
I guess the purpose of this P-switch is to allow me to safely grab the final Yoshi coin.
There's the pipe I went in, but I want to go back just a bit further to get another flower.
I'm so expecting one of these ? blocks to be a multi-coin block.
BGM: Custom - Sithle Woods by MuimiMoji
Well, so much for my fireball idea, and I already tried shelling one of them earlier. If I find another flower, I'll try the fireball idea again.
Gotta check every square inch of the air...
BGM: Touhou 8 - Reisen's Theme - Lunatic Eyes ~ Invisible Full Moon
Ha! That was a nice shot!
Nothing up here, but the screen does scroll up, so I'll want to keep checking up there periodically.

Happy Easter everyone, and welcome back to Lunar Legends! Last time, Dross just stole our dragon diamond, and we have to chase after him through the sewers to get it back! ...Wait, that's a different game.
Alright, there we go!
Huh. The screen dims when you pause in this hack. Okay, now let me quickly get back to where I was before.
Alright, so this path leads to Kiwi Woods 2. No big surprise there. However, which way shall I go next? Let's open up Notepad and find out!
Whoa, close call there.
Uh, oh. I just created cutoff! This hack isn't going to be accepted at SMW Central!
I'm pretty good at video games, by the way.
BARF! Well, I suck, but that's okay. I can get a replacement cape right away! (Hey, that rhymes!)
Well, at least I can take refuge in here for a while, and possibly score scores of 1-ups!

And then I mysteriously forget to try frying those things for some reason... (I checked later off screen, and you can indeed destroy them with fireballs! But, why didn't I try that right away? I really have no idea. My brain must've been farting or something...)
And, just like that, secret exit! I'm guessing I had to fly to reach it, since the game handed me a cape at the start of this level.
No, that wasn't quite a factory there...
Interestingly, this P-switch music speeds up over time.
Whoops! Not what I meant to do there, but that block only had a single coin.
To be continued...
It would help if I could block clone properly...
Okay, so let's see what's in these Kiwi Woods, shall we?
BGM: Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon (Genesis) - Stage 2-2

Ha! They can be killed by the goal! Oh, what? The thing I was carrying transformed into an item this time? That's weird... It hadn't been doing that before... Of course, the extra flower is worthless, but I wonder why it appeared this time...
Yeah, that worked, and it caused a dead Bob-omb to appear, like I was expecting. However, are those things really otherwise unkillable aside from cape spins? Wow, that's kind of nasty...
Yeah, I can cape spin it, but I lost my cape to its shot at the same time... May as well take the flower now.
Wow, nothing above that Lava Lotus's platform? I would've thought that would've been a great hiding spot for something...
Thanks go to Greenman1147 for providing me with that picture.
Hmm... Now I'm wondering... Who would make a better Easter bunny: Reisen, Tewi, or Reisen II?
Man, there's even more of these annoying things! Can I maybe fireball them? Well, first I'd need to get a flower...

Well, this leads to Kiwi Woods 3, which is a yellow level, so I'm not going to hold a vote this time. Will I be finishing off world 2 next time? And will I be holding a vote next time? Will we find out next time? Find out next time!
Well, I guess I'll be playing Kiwi Woods 2 next...
Wow, now I'm really sucking! Good thing for Start+Select!
Screw it. I shouldn't try to make a block factory here. I can accidentally pull off a cool trick shot with that Goomba though!
I wonder if this springboard really was meant for just the secret exit...
And, there's a flower!
I guess it could be used to allow capeless plumbers to reach the secret exit, but I wonder if it has another use elsewhere... Well, may as well check just about everywhere!
Oh, I'd better be careful here. A bad block clone here could cause a brown block to block off the pipe and trap me!
Huh. There's a newcomer. It looks like a Fire Chomp with a pumpkin plant for its head. Attempting to shell it didn't work. Can I cape spin it?
There's another one of those Pumpkin Fire Chomps, and I can't stomp-kill it...
Okay, so let's play this level, which is called... What...

That leads up towards the pipe (which I do auto-move to this time), but I'm not going to check it out yet. I've still got a normal exit to get, and then I have to check the voting results before deciding where to go next.
Alright, screw the block factory attempts for now. Okay, so above here was where the secret exit was, but let's stay on the main path this time.
Interestingly, I caused the victory music to be cutoff by the regular level music by hitting the goal just before the P-switch expired.
Oh, nuts. I should've tried to make a block factory here. Well, maybe next time, since I'll have to play this level at least twice anyway.
BGM: Adventures of Lolo (NES) - Main Theme
Man, why am I having a hard time making block factories lately?
Secret path it is! Let's go through that pipe!
Huh. The game's giving me a springboard here, though I had to be super to reach it.
And now to waste everyone's time trying to make a block factory here. At least I'm wasting time at double speed this time!
Nope, though I bet I can when it explodes.
Alright, 7 lives earned here isn't bad.
OMG! OMG! OMG! It's a cape! Now I can break everything! However, while I will use it to help me explore at times, I think I'll be mostly playing the levels "normally".
Oh, yeah. I notice that the things etched into the dirt of this level are cape feathers. Very fitting.
BGM: SMB3 - P-switch
Oh, hello there, P-switch!

Wow, I can't believe that this game just seriously trolled all of us again! Alright, next time I encounter a red level in this hack, I'm going to scout ahead to see if both paths lead to playable levels before calling for another vote!
